  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "kind": "summary",
        "title": "Summary",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Kronecker product of two arrays."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Computes the Kronecker product, a composite array made of blocks of the\nsecond array scaled by the first."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "parameters",
        "title": "Parameters",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "a, b",
            "type": "array_like",
            "desc_blocks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "returns",
        "title": "Returns",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "out",
            "type": "ndarray",
            "desc_blocks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "notes",
        "title": "Notes",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "The function assumes that the number of dimensions of `a` and `b`\nare the same, if necessary prepending the smallest with ones.\nIf ``a.shape = (r0,r1,..,rN)`` and ``b.shape = (s0,s1,...,sN)``,\nthe Kronecker product has shape ``(r0*s0, r1*s1, ..., rN*SN)``.\nThe elements are products of elements from `a` and `b`, organized\nexplicitly by::"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "    kron(a,b)[k0,k1,...,kN] = a[i0,i1,...,iN] * b[j0,j1,...,jN]"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "where::"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "    kt = it * st + jt,  t = 0,...,N"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "In the common 2-D case (N=1), the block structure can be visualized::"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "    [[ a[0,0]*b,   a[0,1]*b,  ... , a[0,-1]*b  ],\n     [  ...                              ...   ],\n     [ a[-1,0]*b,  a[-1,1]*b, ... , a[-1,-1]*b ]]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "examples",
        "title": "Examples",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> import numpy as np\n>>> np.kron([1,10,100], [5,6,7])\narray([  5,   6,   7, ..., 500, 600, 700])\n>>> np.kron([5,6,7], [1,10,100])\narray([  5,  50, 500, ...,   7,  70, 700])"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> np.kron(np.eye(2), np.ones((2,2)))\narray([[1.,  1.,  0.,  0.],\n       [1.,  1.,  0.,  0.],\n       [0.,  0.,  1.,  1.],\n       [0.,  0.,  1.,  1.]])"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> a = np.arange(100).reshape((2,5,2,5))\n>>> b = np.arange(24).reshape((2,3,4))\n>>> c = np.kron(a,b)\n>>> c.shape\n(2, 10, 6, 20)\n>>> I = (1,3,0,2)\n>>> J = (0,2,1)\n>>> J1 = (0,) + J             # extend to ndim=4\n>>> S1 = (1,) + b.shape\n>>> K = tuple(np.array(I) * np.array(S1) + np.array(J1))\n>>> c[K] == a[I]*b[J]\nTrue"
          }
        ]
      },
